oracle.kv.stats

Interface StoreIteratorMetrics


  • public interface StoreIteratorMetrics
    Interface to the stats and metrics associated with a KVS storeIterator operation.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      long getAverageBlockedResultsQueueGetTime()
      Returns the average time (in milliseconds) spent waiting for Results Queue take() operations, exclusive of the first take() operation.
      long getAverageBlockedResultsQueuePutTime()
      Returns the average time (in milliseconds) spent waiting for put() operations to the Results Queue.
      long getBlockedResultsQueueGets()
      Returns the number of Results Queue take() operations on the application side which have blocked.
      long getBlockedResultsQueuePuts()
      Returns the number of put() operations to the Results Queue on the producer side of the queue which have blocked.
      long getMaxBlockedResultsQueueGetTime()
      Returns the maximum time (in milliseconds) spent waiting for Results Queue take() operations, exclusive of the first take() operation.
      long getMaxBlockedResultsQueuePutTime()
      Returns the maximum time (in milliseconds) spent waiting for put() operations to the Results Queue.
      long getMinBlockedResultsQueueGetTime()
      Returns the minimum time (in milliseconds) spent waiting for Results Queue take() operations, exclusive of the first take() operation.
      long getMinBlockedResultsQueuePutTime()
      Returns the minimum time (in milliseconds) spent waiting for put() operations to the Results Queue.

    • Method Detail

      • getBlockedResultsQueuePuts

        long getBlockedResultsQueuePuts()
        Returns the number of put() operations to the Results Queue on the producer side of the queue which have blocked.

        Blocked Results Queue put operations occur when the client side can't process results as fast as the parallel scan threads receive them from the Replication Nodes.

      • getAverageBlockedResultsQueuePutTime

        long getAverageBlockedResultsQueuePutTime()
        Returns the average time (in milliseconds) spent waiting for put() operations to the Results Queue.

        Blocked Results Queue put operations occur when the client side can't process results as fast as the parallel scan threads receive them from the Replication Nodes.

      • getMinBlockedResultsQueuePutTime

        long getMinBlockedResultsQueuePutTime()
        Returns the minimum time (in milliseconds) spent waiting for put() operations to the Results Queue.

        Blocked Results Queue put operations occur when the client side can't process results as fast as the parallel scan threads receive them from the Replication Nodes.

      • getMaxBlockedResultsQueuePutTime

        long getMaxBlockedResultsQueuePutTime()
        Returns the maximum time (in milliseconds) spent waiting for put() operations to the Results Queue.

        Blocked Results Queue put operations occur when the client side can't process results as fast as the parallel scan threads receive them from the Replication Nodes.

      • getBlockedResultsQueueGets

        long getBlockedResultsQueueGets()
        Returns the number of Results Queue take() operations on the application side which have blocked. This number does not include the first take() operation on the queue.

        Blocked Results Queue take operations occur when the Replication Nodes can't produce results as fast as the application is able to process them.

      • getAverageBlockedResultsQueueGetTime

        long getAverageBlockedResultsQueueGetTime()
        Returns the average time (in milliseconds) spent waiting for Results Queue take() operations, exclusive of the first take() operation.

        Blocked Results Queue take operations occur when the Replication Nodes can't produce results as fast as the application is able to process them.

      • getMinBlockedResultsQueueGetTime

        long getMinBlockedResultsQueueGetTime()
        Returns the minimum time (in milliseconds) spent waiting for Results Queue take() operations, exclusive of the first take() operation.

        Blocked Results Queue take operations occur when the Replication Nodes can't produce results as fast as the application is able to process them.

      • getMaxBlockedResultsQueueGetTime

        long getMaxBlockedResultsQueueGetTime()
        Returns the maximum time (in milliseconds) spent waiting for Results Queue take() operations, exclusive of the first take() operation.

        Blocked Results Queue take operations occur when the Replication Nodes can't produce results as fast as the application is able to process them.
